cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CE, cs.CR, cs.HC 

This paper deals with the ethical considerations of using social media data in health research and proposes a machine learning approach to automate consent decisions. The paper discusses technical and ethical implications of the proposed approach. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.CY (Computers and Society) as the paper deals with ethical considerations of using machine learning in health research. Other likely sub-categories include cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the paper deals with social media data, cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) as the paper proposes a machine learning approach, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the paper discusses data leaks, and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as the paper discusses user study and real-world implications.
